Japan's Nippon Oil Co. Ltd. said Friday its pre-tax  earnings fell 2.6 percent from a year earlier to 42.3 billion yen (411 million  dollars) in the year to March and forecast a further decline this year.
The country's largest distributor of petroleum products said sales dropped  9.5 percent in the same period to 1,806 billion yen.
Nippon Oil, which operates a joint venture with Caltex of the United  States, projected a smaller profit of 35 billion yen in the current year with  sales forecast to edge down to 1,800 billion yen.
